issue.title: Issues loading grafana data
issue.body:
Hi,

I'd like to use this tool to help find unused metrics and reduce cardinality of our cortex.

We're on grafana v8.5.15.

I'm getting parsing errors when trying to load the dashboards from grafana
```bash
/cortextool analyse grafana --address=http://monitoring-grafana.monitoring.svc.cluster.local --key=<redacted>
unmarshal board: json: cannot unmarshal object into Go struct field Row.rows.panels of type []struct { Type string "json:\"type,omitempty\""; Params []string "json:\"params,omitempty\"" } for gJ39gv2Mz AWS ElastiCache Redis
unmarshal board: json: cannot unmarshal object into Go struct field Board.panels of type []struct { Type string "json:\"type,omitempty\""; Params []string "json:\"params,omitempty\"" } for AWSRDSdbi AWS RDS
unmarshal board: json: cannot unmarshal number 4.8 into Go struct field Board.panels of type int for Zb91tPK4z Cloud Sync Performance
unmarshal board: json: cannot unmarshal string into Go struct field Row.rows.panels of type bool for fa49a4706d07a042595b664c87fb33ea Kubernetes / Nodes
unmarshal board: json: cannot unmarshal object into Go struct field Board.panels of type string for DqWgOchnk PostgreSQL Exporter
```

issue.title: Analyze cortex failure
issue.body:
To avoid large queries, we've set a limit to the number of series a query can hit

```bash
./cortextool analyse prometheus \
    --address=https://internal-cortex.../ \
    --id=<redacted> \
    --key=<redacted> \
    --log.level=debug \
    --grafana-metrics-file="metrics-in-grafana.json"
DEBU[0025] in use cortex_request_duration_seconds_count 2 
DEBU[0025] in use cortex_ring_members 60                
DEBU[0025] in use cortex_s3_request_duration_seconds_count 0 
DEBU[0025] in use cs_error_counter 3                    
DEBU[0025] in use db_mat_view_query_duration_count 750  
cortextool: error: error querying count by (job) (db_model_duration_bucket): execution: expanding series: the query hit the max number of series limit (limit: 100000 series), try --help
```

is there anyway we can just skip this metrics rather than have the whole analysis fail?

release.name: v0.11.0
release.body:
# v0.11.0 Release

## Changes

* [FEATURE] Support Arm64 on Darwin for all binaries (benchtool etc). #215
* [BUGFIX] Fix `cortextool rules` legends displaying wrong symbols for updates and deletions. #226
* [CHANGE] Upgrade modules to latest versions #277

## Removals

This version removes support for chunk-tool following removal of chunk storage support in cortex.
Benchtool is also not released as a part of this version. 

## Installation

## cortextool

```console
# download the binary (adapt os and arch as needed)
$ curl -fSL -o "cortextool" "https://github.com/grafana/cortex-tools/releases/download/v0.11.0/cortextool_v0.11.0_Linux_x86_64"

# make it executable
$ chmod a+x "cortextool"

# have fun :)
$ ./cortextool --help
```

commits.message: Downgrade loki and dskit to fix duplicate proto errors (#279)

pull_request.title: Downgrade loki and dskit to fix duplicate proto errors
pull_request.body:
The latest versions of loki required dskit and weaveworks/common both brought protos with same namespace and name that created conflicts resulting in errors like - 
```
2023/09/06 15:12:21 proto: duplicate proto type registered: httpgrpc.HTTPRequest
2023/09/06 15:12:21 proto: duplicate proto type registered: httpgrpc.HTTPResponse
2023/09/06 15:12:21 proto: duplicate proto type registered: httpgrpc.Header
```

This PR brings the versions back when dskit copied over the changes.

pull_request.title: Change dskit and loki to fix proto conflicts
pull_request.body:
Change versions of dskit and loki to resolve proto errors.

Had to rename protos within httpgrpc package in dskit as they're copied over directly from weaveworks/common. When both modules are imported (dskit and weaveworks/common) they result in duplicate protos. 
From what I could find, there are not many ways this could be resolved cleanly.

DSKit - https://github.com/grafana/dskit/compare/main...temp-change-proto-name
Loki- https://github.com/grafana/loki/compare/main...temp-proto-fix
